Side plank with reach.Description: Begin in a side plank position with your feet stacked and a kettlebell in your top hand, arm extended towards the ceiling. Engage your core and glutes to maintain stability, then slowly reach the kettlebell under your torso, rotating your upper body slightly, before returning to the starting position. Focus on maintaining a straight line from head to heels and avoid letting your hips drop.

Plank with toe taps.Description: Begin in a forearm plank position with a resistance loop band around your ankles, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core and glutes, then slowly tap your right foot out to the side, return to center, and repeat with the left foot, maintaining tension in the band throughout. Focus on keeping hips stable and avoid sagging or lifting them too high.

Mountain climbers with sliders.Description: Begin in a high plank position with your hands on the ab wheel and feet on sliders. Engage your core and maintain a straight line from head to heels as you alternately drive your knees towards your chest, keeping your hips low and stable. Focus on controlled movements to maximize core engagement and avoid excessive hip movement.

Single-leg V-ups.Description: Begin by lying on your back with a dumbbell in each hand, arms extended overhead, and legs straight. Engage your core to lift one leg and your upper body simultaneously, reaching the dumbbells towards your toes, then slowly lower back to the starting position. Focus on maintaining a controlled movement to effectively target the core and hip flexors.

Plank with hip dips.Description: Begin in a forearm plank position with your feet elevated on a plyo box, ensuring your body forms a straight line from shoulders to heels. Rotate your hips to one side, gently dipping them towards the floor, then return to the center and repeat on the opposite side. Focus on engaging your core and obliques throughout the movement to maintain stability and control.

Star jumps.Description: Begin by standing with feet shoulder-width apart, a resistance band looped around your ankles. Jump into the air, spreading your legs wide and raising your arms overhead, creating a star shape. Land softly with knees slightly bent, returning to the starting position, focusing on maintaining tension in the band to engage the glutes and thighs.

Russian twists with medicine ball.Description: Sit on the floor with knees bent and feet flat, holding a medicine ball with both hands. Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight, and lift your feet off the ground. Rotate your torso to the right, bringing the medicine ball beside your hip, then twist to the left, engaging your core throughout the movement.

Side plank with leg lifts.Description: Begin in a side plank position with your forearm on the ground and a kettlebell resting on your top hip. Engage your core and lift your top leg while maintaining a straight line from head to heels, ensuring the kettlebell remains stable. Focus on keeping your hips elevated and aligned throughout the movement to target the obliques and glutes effectively.

Plank with arm extension.Description: Begin in a plank position with your feet on core sliders, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Extend one arm forward while maintaining a stable core, then return it to the starting position and repeat with the other arm, keeping hips level throughout. Focus on engaging the core, shoulders, and stabilizing muscles to maintain balance.

Jump squats.Description: Begin by standing on a plyo box with feet shoulder-width apart. Lower into a squat, then explosively jump off the box, landing softly on the ground with knees slightly bent to absorb impact. Focus on engaging the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes throughout the movement.

Dead bug.Description: Begin by lying on your back with your arms extended above your shoulders, holding the ab wheel. Lift your legs so your knees are bent at 90 degrees, aligning them over your hips. Slowly extend one leg towards the floor while simultaneously rolling the ab wheel overhead, keeping your core engaged and lower back pressed into the ground. Return to the starting position and repeat on the opposite side.

Lunge jumps.Description: Begin in a standing position with a resistance band looped around your thighs, just above the knees. Step one foot forward into a lunge, ensuring your front knee aligns over your ankle, then explosively jump and switch legs mid-air, landing softly in a lunge with the opposite leg forward. Focus on maintaining balance and control, engaging your core and glutes throughout the movement.

Bosu ball mountain climbers.Description: Begin in a high plank position with your hands on a medicine ball placed on a Bosu ball, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Drive your knees alternately towards your chest in a controlled manner, maintaining core stability and balance throughout the movement. Focus on engaging your core, shoulders, and legs to enhance stability and coordination.

Plank with knee to elbow.Description: Begin in a high plank position with hands gripping kettlebell handles, ensuring wrists are aligned under shoulders. Engage your core and bring one knee towards the same-side elbow, then return to the starting position and alternate sides. Focus on maintaining a straight line from head to heels and avoid letting hips sag or rise.

Squat with oblique twist.Description: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, loop the resistance band around your thighs just above the knees. Lower into a squat, keeping your chest up and knees aligned with toes. As you rise, twist your torso to one side, engaging your obliques, then return to the squat position and repeat on the other side.

Pike push-ups.Description: Begin in a plank position with hands on the ab wheel, feet together, and hips raised to form an inverted V-shape. Roll the wheel forward while lowering your head towards the ground, keeping elbows close to your body, then push back to the starting position. Focus on engaging your shoulders, triceps, and core throughout the movement.

Lateral bounds.Description: Stand beside a plyo box with feet shoulder-width apart. Push off your outside foot to jump laterally over the box, landing softly on the opposite side with knees slightly bent. Focus on explosive power and balance, engaging the glutes, quads, and calves.

Body saw.Description: Begin in a forearm plank position with your feet on core sliders, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core and slide your body backward by extending your arms, then return to the starting position by pulling your body forward, maintaining a stable plank throughout. Focus on controlled movements to effectively target the core muscles.

Plank with alternating leg lifts.Description: Begin in a forearm plank position with a resistance band looped around your ankles, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core and glutes as you lift one leg off the ground, keeping it straight, then lower it back down and repeat with the other leg. Focus on maintaining stability and control throughout the movement to effectively target the core, glutes, and hamstrings.

Squat jumps with medicine ball.Description: Begin in a standing position with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a medicine ball close to your chest. Lower into a squat by bending your knees and pushing your hips back, then explosively jump upwards, extending your arms overhead with the ball. Land softly back into the squat position, ensuring your knees are aligned with your toes throughout the movement.

Side plank with twist.Description: Begin in a side plank position with your forearm on the ground and feet stacked, holding a kettlebell in your top hand. Engage your core and lift your hips, then rotate your torso to bring the kettlebell under your body, returning to the starting position. Focus on maintaining a straight line from head to heels and controlled movements to engage the obliques and shoulders effectively.

Flutter kicks with weight plate.Description: Lie on your back with a weight plate held securely against your chest, legs extended. Lift your legs slightly off the ground and perform a fluttering motion by alternating kicks, keeping your core engaged and lower back pressed into the floor. Focus on maintaining a steady pace and controlled movement to target the lower abs and hip flexors effectively.
Flutter kicks with weight plate.Muscles: Lower abs, hip flexors, and core stabilizers.

Plank with leg rotation.Description: Begin in a forearm plank position with core sliders under your feet, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core and rotate your hips to one side, sliding one foot outward while keeping the other stable, then return to the center and repeat on the opposite side. Focus on maintaining a stable upper body and controlled movements to effectively engage the obliques and core muscles.

Bear crawls.Description: Begin in a plank position with your hands on the plyo box and feet on the ground, keeping your body aligned from head to heels. Engage your core and move forward by simultaneously stepping your right hand and left foot, then your left hand and right foot, maintaining a low, controlled movement. Focus on keeping your hips stable and your back flat throughout the exercise.

Leg pull-ins.Description: Begin in a plank position with your hands on the ground and feet on the ab wheel. Engage your core and roll the wheel towards your hands by bending your knees, keeping your back straight, then extend your legs back to the starting position. Focus on maintaining a stable core throughout the movement to effectively target the abdominals and hip flexors.

Jumping lunges.Description: Begin in a standing position with a resistance band looped around your thighs, just above the knees. Step into a lunge position, ensuring your front knee is aligned over your ankle, then explosively jump and switch legs mid-air, landing softly in a lunge on the opposite side. Focus on maintaining tension in the band to engage your glutes and thighs throughout the movement.

Side plank with crunch.Description: Begin in a side plank position with your forearm on the ground and feet stacked, holding a medicine ball with your top hand. Engage your core as you bring the medicine ball towards your chest, performing a crunch by drawing your top knee towards your elbow, then return to the starting position. Focus on maintaining a straight line from head to heels and avoid letting your hips drop.

Plank with lateral arm raise.Description: Begin in a plank position with feet hip-width apart and a kettlebell in each hand, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core and slowly lift one kettlebell to the side, keeping your arm straight and parallel to the floor, then return to the starting position and repeat on the other side. Focus on maintaining stability and control throughout the movement to effectively target the core, shoulders, and upper back.

Mountain climbers with kettlebells.Description: Begin in a high plank position with each hand gripping a kettlebell, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Drive one knee towards your chest, then quickly switch legs, maintaining a brisk pace while keeping your core engaged and kettlebells stable. Focus on maintaining proper form to engage the core, shoulders, and legs effectively.

Scapular push-ups.Description: Begin in a high plank position with hands on the ab wheel, arms extended, and core engaged. Keeping arms straight, retract your shoulder blades by squeezing them together, then protract by pushing them apart, maintaining a stable core throughout. Focus on controlled movements to effectively engage the scapular stabilizers and core muscles.

Tuck jumps.Description: Stand on a plyo box with feet shoulder-width apart, arms at your sides. Jump off the box, tucking your knees towards your chest while in mid-air, and land softly on the ground with knees slightly bent. Focus on explosive power and control, engaging your core and leg muscles throughout the movement.

Plank with bird dog.Description: Begin in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and feet on core sliders. Extend your right arm forward and your left leg backward simultaneously, keeping your core engaged and body stable. Return to the starting position and alternate sides, focusing on maintaining a straight line from head to heels.

Squat jumps with kettlebells.Description: Begin in a standing position with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at your sides. Lower into a squat by bending your knees and pushing your hips back, then explosively jump upwards, extending your arms overhead. Land softly back into the squat position, ensuring your knees are aligned with your toes, focusing on engaging your quadriceps, glutes, and core throughout the movement.

Side plank with leg raise.Description: Begin in a side plank position with your forearm on the ground and a medicine ball placed between your feet. Engage your core and lift your hips off the ground, maintaining a straight line from head to heels. While keeping your body stable, raise the top leg, squeezing the medicine ball, then lower it back down with control.

Plank with reach through.Description: Begin in a plank position with your hands on the kettlebells, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core and reach one arm through to touch the opposite kettlebell, then return to the starting position and repeat with the other arm. Focus on maintaining stability and control throughout the movement to effectively target the core, shoulders, and stabilizing muscles.

Mountain climbers with dumbbells.Description: Begin in a high plank position with a dumbbell in each hand, ensuring your wrists are directly under your shoulders. Drive one knee towards your chest while keeping the other leg extended, then quickly switch legs in a running motion, maintaining a strong core and stable upper body. Focus on maintaining a steady pace and controlled movement to engage the core, shoulders, and legs effectively.

Squat jumps with dumbbells.Description: Begin in a standing position with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. Lower into a squat by bending your knees and pushing your hips back, then explosively jump upwards, extending your arms overhead. Land softly back into the squat position, ensuring your knees are aligned with your toes to engage the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes effectively.

Plank with alternating arm and leg lift.Description: Begin in a plank position with your hands on the core sliders, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Simultaneously lift your right arm and left leg, keeping your core engaged and hips stable, then return to the starting position and alternate sides. Focus on maintaining balance and control throughout the movement to effectively engage the core, shoulders, and glutes.

Side plank with row.Description: Begin in a side plank position with your forearm on the ground and feet stacked, holding a kettlebell in your top hand. Engage your core and keep your body in a straight line as you perform a rowing motion by pulling the kettlebell towards your ribcage, focusing on squeezing your shoulder blade. Maintain stability throughout the movement to effectively target the obliques, shoulders, and upper back.

Plank with side leg lift.Description: Begin in a plank position with forearms on a medicine ball, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core and lift one leg to the side, keeping it straight, then return to the starting position and alternate legs. Focus on maintaining balance and stability throughout the movement.

Mountain climbers with resistance bands.Description: Begin in a high plank position with a resistance band looped around your feet, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Drive one knee towards your chest, then quickly switch legs, maintaining a brisk pace while keeping your core engaged and hips level. Focus on maintaining tension in the band to enhance the workout for your core, shoulders, and legs.

Squat jumps with resistance bands.Description: Begin by placing the resistance band just above your knees and standing with feet shoulder-width apart. Lower into a squat position, ensuring your knees do not extend past your toes, then explosively jump upwards, landing softly back into the squat position. Focus on maintaining tension in the band throughout the movement to engage the glutes, quads, and hamstrings effectively.

Plank with knee drives.Description: Begin in a high plank position with hands gripping kettlebell handles, ensuring wrists are aligned under shoulders. Engage your core and drive one knee towards your chest, then return to starting position and alternate legs, maintaining a stable torso throughout. Focus on core stability and shoulder strength while keeping your hips level.

Side plank with overhead press.Description: Begin in a side plank position with your body in a straight line, supporting yourself on one forearm and stacking your feet. Hold a dumbbell in your free hand, extend your arm straight up, and press the dumbbell overhead while maintaining core stability. Focus on engaging your obliques, shoulders, and core throughout the movement.

Plank with mountain climbers.Description: Start in a high plank position with hands gripping kettlebell handles, ensuring wrists are aligned under shoulders. Engage your core and alternate driving knees towards your chest in a controlled manner, maintaining a steady pace and keeping hips level. Focus on core stability and shoulder strength throughout the movement.

Mountain climbers with ankle weights.Description: Begin in a high plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels. With ankle weights secured, drive one knee towards your chest, then quickly switch legs in a running motion, keeping your core engaged and hips level. This exercise intensifies cardiovascular endurance and targets the core, shoulders, and legs.

Squat jumps with ankle weights.Description: Begin in a standing position with feet shoulder-width apart, wearing ankle weights. Lower into a squat by bending your knees and pushing your hips back, then explosively jump upwards, extending your legs fully. Land softly back into the squat position, ensuring your knees are aligned with your toes to engage the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes effectively.

Plank with jackknife.Description: Begin in a plank position with hands gripping kettlebell handles, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core as you jump your feet apart and then back together, maintaining stability and control throughout the movement. Focus on keeping your hips level and avoid letting them sag or rise.

Side plank with lateral raise.Description: Begin in a side plank position with your body in a straight line, supporting yourself on one forearm and stacking your feet. Hold a dumbbell in your free hand, and with control, raise it laterally until your arm is parallel to the floor, then lower it back down. Focus on engaging your core, shoulders, and obliques throughout the movement.

Plank with spiderman crunch.Description: Start in a high plank position with hands gripping kettlebell handles, ensuring wrists are aligned under shoulders. Engage your core and bring your right knee towards your right elbow, then return to the starting position and repeat on the left side. Focus on maintaining a stable torso and controlled movement to effectively target the core, obliques, and shoulders.

Mountain climbers with core sliders.Description: Begin in a high plank position with each foot on a core slider, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core and alternately slide each knee towards your chest, maintaining a brisk pace while keeping your hips level and shoulders over wrists. Focus on maintaining a controlled movement to effectively target the core, shoulders, and legs.

Squat jumps with core sliders.Description: Begin in a standing position with each foot on a core slider, feet shoulder-width apart. Lower into a squat by bending your knees and pushing your hips back, then explosively jump up while sliding your feet outward, landing softly back into the squat position. Focus on engaging your core and maintaining balance throughout the movement.

Plank with bicycle crunches.Description: Begin in a plank position with each hand gripping a kettlebell, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core as you bring one knee towards the opposite elbow, alternating sides in a controlled manner, while maintaining stability on the kettlebells. Focus on keeping your hips level and your core engaged throughout the movement to effectively target the abdominals and obliques.

Side plank with front raise.Description: Begin in a side plank position with your body in a straight line, supporting yourself on one forearm and stacking your feet. Hold a dumbbell in your top hand, and with a controlled motion, raise your arm in front of you to shoulder height, keeping your core engaged and hips lifted. Focus on maintaining stability throughout the movement to target the obliques, shoulders, and core.

Plank with cross-body mountain climbers.Description: Begin in a high plank position with each hand gripping a kettlebell, ensuring wrists are aligned under shoulders. Drive one knee towards the opposite elbow, alternating sides while maintaining a stable core and keeping hips level. Focus on engaging the core, shoulders, and obliques throughout the movement.

Mountain climbers with ab wheel.Description: Begin in a high plank position with hands gripping the ab wheel, ensuring your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core and alternately drive your knees towards your chest, maintaining stability and control of the wheel. Focus on keeping your hips level and avoid letting them sag or rise.

Squat jumps with ab wheel.Description: Begin in a standing position with feet shoulder-width apart, holding the ab wheel with both hands. Lower into a squat, then explosively jump upwards while extending the ab wheel forward, landing softly back into the squat position. Focus on engaging the core, quadriceps, and glutes throughout the movement.

Plank.Description: Start in a push-up position with elbows directly under shoulders, body forming a straight line from head to heels. Engage core and hold position for the desired duration.

Side plank.Description: Lie on your side with your legs straight and stacked, resting on the mat. Prop your upper body on your forearm, lift your hips off the ground, and hold your body in a straight line from head to heels, engaging your core and glutes.

Russian twist.Description: Sit on the floor with your knees bent and feet lifted off the ground. Hold a dumbbell with both hands, lean back slightly, and rotate your torso to the right, then to the left, engaging your core throughout the movement. Focus on controlled movements to target the obliques effectively.

Exercise ball rollouts.Description: Start in a kneeling position with your hands on the exercise ball, keeping your core engaged. Roll the ball forward while extending your body, then pull the ball back to the starting position, focusing on controlling the movement to activate your core.
